    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2001 BMW M3 (E46) in impeccable condition. This chassis features the legendary S54B32 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Double VANOS system to deliver a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. The Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox provides crisp engagement, paired with a variable M differential lock for optimal torque distribution. Mechanically, this vehicle is superlative: the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced, and rod bearings were replaced as preventative maintenance to ensure long-term reciprocating assembly integrity. The suspension geometry remains factory-true, utilizing OE-spec bushings and dampers to preserve the communicative steering rack and 50/50 weight distribution. No signs of thermal cycling on engine plastics, zero fluid seepage, and a factory-original finish throughout.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 41
    },
    {
